1. Primary Engine Operations (Scanning & Modes)
Standard Discovery Scan: python backend/main.py (Executes a single cycle pipeline to extract standard configurations.)
Mock / Simulation Mode: python backend/main.py --mode MOCK (Uses LocalStack and Azurite, meaning you don't need real API credentials or internet access.)
Live Target Mode: python backend/main.py --mode LIVE (Forces extraction directly against Live Azure and AWS target grids — requires active identities.)
Continuous Daemon Service: python backend/main.py --daemon (Constantly runs the Sovereign-Forensic pipeline at the interval set in your settings.yaml.)
2. Maintenance & Pre-Flights
System Pre-Flight Health Table: python backend/main.py --health (Shows the new Glassy Rich interface tables validating packages, Docker integrity, Python, and Config states before launching.)
Initialize Database Constraints: python backend/main.py --schema (Pushes required index constraints to the Neo4j Graph DB before a large initial extraction.)
3. Destruction & Reset Utilities
Atomic Environment Flush: python backend/scripts/soft_reset.py (Wipes all connected Docker volumes, kills the LocalStack emulator instances, and deletes the forensics ledger securely without destroying code.)
Graph Pruning: python backend/src/utils/db_tools.py --gc (Runs a garbage collection script on Neo4j to delete orphaned aliases and fragmented metadata.)
4. Testing & Forging (Seeding)
Automated Verification: pytest backend/tests/ (Runs any and all configured PyTest assertions targeting the internal pipeline modules.)
Forge Graph Seeds (Simulation): python backend/src/simulation/enterprise_seeder.py (Spins up randomized tenant profiles, Vnets, and spoofed Subscriptions directly bypassing API limits to stress test the UI.)



